Public":true,"bio":"Low noise. High conviction. Let outcomes confirm.","proxyWallet":"0xd8c95ad7b7aa4a3ffbbd779b0bf80da5faaee4b3","baseAddress":"0x88f84aa189dbf9d7c0345f69de6f4fc966e7aa51","profileImage":"https://polymarket-upload.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/profile-image-7483366-c1964503-33f6-4bfb-91a7-75858ad6187b.webp"},"reactions":[{"id":"2810516","commentID":2849400,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x6aba547b01f9305a6e89390dba7090f4f3f34886","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xe5052db3c454e1235fd19cd662e129234e26600c"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":1},{"id":"2849403","body":"What does that mean?","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"parentCommentID":"2849252","userAddress":"0x6aba547b01f9305a6e89390dba7090f4f3f34886","replyAddress":"0xec019dc1565245ddb33fb663bb2d2ca79cfd8205","createdAt":"2026-04-27T11:41:08.279352Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T11:41:18.905361Z","profile":{"name":"brooooookz","pseudonym":"Willing-Haven","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0xe5052db3c454e1235fd19cd662e129234e26600c","baseAddress":"0x6aba547b01f9305a6e89390dba7090f4f3f34886","profileImage":"https://polymarket-upload.s3.us-east-2.amazonaws.com/profile-image-7189392-555f3303-15e6-450e-b3d7-04abceff6a3d.png"},"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":0},{"id":"2849198","body":"What kind of nonsense is this from the UMA discussions? From exactly the same perspective, we could say the market closed in favor of \"yes,\" and the investment market shouldn't concern us—it's a forecast market, after all!AI Summary\nP1 (No)\n•\nSupporters contend that a platform clarification indicates this should resolve to P1 (No), asserting the question is already settled.\n•\nProponents argue from a trading/ROI angle that backing P1 is preferable, citing expected returns from bond holding or splitting positions and the limited remaining days to resolution.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"userAddress":"0x9b3e7392478760c9c05dc59c2ceb8c9e5e287ca3","createdAt":"2026-04-27T10:08:09.520641Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T10:08:20.300203Z","profile":{"name":"Golovarrr","pseudonym":"Delicious-Reverse","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0xc144a4aa27e18ec1eeb95756921f4a8f0172fbc2","baseAddress":"0x9b3e7392478760c9c05dc59c2ceb8c9e5e287ca3"},"reactions":[{"id":"2810323","commentID":2849198,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x01fe4030b5162c33fcbd1753fa9957486d744d17","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x9a817c446ca66b8859e77f4716a785dc7e76d324"}},{"id":"2810369","commentID":2849198,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x81bcc5dfb03cda6ba49c2f0704661d6de5125f8b","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x51608380dffa9080cd25e4ce9bc249d3dd2fb803"}},{"id":"2810522","commentID":2849198,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x2e41dff9014822c97fd4bd5bf303e84eecf239cc","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xccf31ea0f5de9c0bb4bb695fc77c3683dee41dd9"}},{"id":"2810517","commentID":2849198,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x6aba547b01f9305a6e89390dba7090f4f3f34886","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xe5052db3c454e1235fd19cd662e129234e26600c"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":4},{"id":"2849148","body":"1. The \"Media Consensus\" Clause as an Independent Satisfactor\nThe market rules explicitly provide an alternative path to resolution: \"...or for an official extension... to be otherwise confirmed by an overwhelming consensus of media reporting.\" * Argument: This clause exists specifically for scenarios where formal diplomatic paperwork is delayed or opaque. As of April 22, 11:59 PM ET, Tier 1 news organizations—including Al Jazeera, Reuters, and leading regional outlets like Dawn—reported the extension as a factual reality.\n\nThe \"NO\" Trap: Opponents argue for the \"Both Governments\" confirmation. However, the rule uses the operator \"OR,\" meaning media consensus is a self-sufficient trigger for a \"YES\" resolution, regardless of the availability of a signed document from Tehran.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"userAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8","createdAt":"2026-04-27T09:46:27.751612Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T09:46:37.910282Z","profile":{"name":"0x920ab2760C5B4BE099328665E45Bb833d30D32C9-1773892601412","pseudonym":"Boring-Comportment","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0x920ab2760c5b4be099328665e45bb833d30d32c9","baseAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8"},"reactions":[{"id":"2810910","commentID":2849148,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x1901a32d6264e24d8291166b887dd4af6507ade7","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x918f4872e2675144bbe8c1db33069db57ff566ad"}},{"id":"2810276","commentID":2849148,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0"}},{"id":"2810271","commentID":2849148,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0"}},{"id":"2810353","commentID":2849148,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x037ef70a56897f9087464744cb587b4e8986bd9b","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xe58b4aa41a1218569d0ea5503d5b4b20fccb4581"}},{"id":"2810359","commentID":2849148,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x01fe4030b5162c33fcbd1753fa9957486d744d17","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x9a817c446ca66b8859e77f4716a785dc7e76d324"}},{"id":"2810529","commentID":2849148,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x6aba547b01f9305a6e89390dba7090f4f3f34886","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xe5052db3c454e1235fd19cd662e129234e26600c"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":6},{"id":"2849149","body":"2. Consistency and The \"April 7 Precedent\" (Agency Theory)\nOracles must maintain procedural consistency to ensure market integrity.\n\nFact: The original April 7 ceasefire was established through the mediation of Pakistan. There was no dual-signed public treaty; it was confirmed via the mediator.\n\nArgument: On April 22, Pakistani PM Shehbaz Sharif officially announced that both parties had reached an agreement to extend the halt in hostilities. If the market accepted the April 7 agreement via Pakistan as the baseline for \"YES,\" it is logically inconsistent and biased to reject the April 22 extension announced through the exact same diplomatic channel. Pakistan acted as the authorized proxy for both nations.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"parentCommentID":"2849148","userAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8","replyAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8","createdAt":"2026-04-27T09:46:37.63849Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T09:46:49.045087Z","profile":{"name":"0x920ab2760C5B4BE099328665E45Bb833d30D32C9-1773892601412","pseudonym":"Boring-Comportment","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0x920ab2760c5b4be099328665e45bb833d30d32c9","baseAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8"},"reactions":[{"id":"2810274","commentID":2849149,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0"}},{"id":"2810533","commentID":2849149,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x6aba547b01f9305a6e89390dba7090f4f3f34886","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xe5052db3c454e1235fd19cd662e129234e26600c"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":2},{"id":"2849153","body":"3. Discrediting Negative Noise (Political Rhetoric vs. Official Rejection)\n\"NO\" supporters often cite social media posts from Iranian advisors (e.g., Mahdi Mohammadi) claiming the extension was \"meaningless.\"\n\nRebuttal: Under international law and the specific rules of this market, informal comments from \"advisors\" on social media do not constitute an official government rejection.\n\nStatus Quo: At the deadline, the Iranian Foreign Ministry had NOT issued a formal denial of the extension. In the absence of a formal \"NO\" and the presence of an overwhelming \"YES\" from the authorized mediator and global media, the default logical resolution based on the provided rules is YES.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"parentCommentID":"2849148","userAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8","replyAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8","createdAt":"2026-04-27T09:47:58.53671Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T09:48:08.860007Z","profile":{"name":"0x920ab2760C5B4BE099328665E45Bb833d30D32C9-1773892601412","pseudonym":"Boring-Comportment","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0x920ab2760c5b4be099328665e45bb833d30d32c9","baseAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8"},"reactions":[{"id":"2810273","commentID":2849153,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0"}},{"id":"2810275","commentID":2849153,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":2},{"id":"2849155","body":"Conclusion: To resolve this as \"NO\" would be to ignore the explicit \"Media Consensus\" provision and the established precedent of the mediator's role. For the sake of oracle reliability, this market must resolve as YES.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"parentCommentID":"2849148","userAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8","replyAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8","createdAt":"2026-04-27T09:48:39.313526Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T09:48:49.578499Z","profile":{"name":"0x920ab2760C5B4BE099328665E45Bb833d30D32C9-1773892601412","pseudonym":"Boring-Comportment","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0x920ab2760c5b4be099328665e45bb833d30d32c9","baseAddress":"0xa1ce01664fa6d4c6a75210cd35b4f263f05138b8"},"reactions":[{"id":"2810272","commentID":2849155,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":1},{"id":"2849128","body":"\"Both extensions of the April 7 ceasefire AND new agreements for an extended ceasefire\" and \"or for an official extension of the ceasefire agreement in place to be otherwise confirmed by an overwhelming consensus of media reporting.\" The official clarification from poly market seems to not take THIS INTO account and contradicts it instead sticking only to the first condition upon which the market resolves yes or no. MERELY AN OFFICIAL EXTENSION IS SUFFICIENT. Instead they are applying for requirement from the first test for public confirmation to the second test which is the media recognition of an official extension, only the official extension in the clear mutual government acknowledgement clause requires clear government acknowledgement.","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"userAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c","createdAt":"2026-04-27T09:42:43.647009Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T09:42:54.847798Z","profile":{"name":"Jupiter1488","pseudonym":"Trusting-Chord","displayUsernamePublic":true,"proxyWallet":"0x12b11f6c0cd32c1e7b759e7a5bc4603632da61b0","baseAddress":"0xcf4408bb0aa8ad275befd4a204c88c6b0a05824c"},"reactions":[{"id":"2810282","commentID":2849128,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x3d75d0660ad2574e74f6ffc169030819f8e0aac9","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xf8eb681fb8909496dc15aea5b233b310e2db8473"}},{"id":"2810283","commentID":2849128,"reactionType":"HEART","userAddress":"0x3d75d0660ad2574e74f6ffc169030819f8e0aac9","profile":{"proxyWallet":"0xf8eb681fb8909496dc15aea5b233b310e2db8473"}}],"reportCount":0,"reactionCount":2},{"id":"2849093","body":"Can somebody give me details of which discord they discuss all this","parentEntityType":"Event","parentEntityID":357625,"userAddress":"0x88f84aa189dbf9d7c0345f69de6f4fc966e7aa51","createdAt":"2026-04-27T09:28:41.383477Z","updatedAt":"2026-04-27T09:28:51.774843Z","profile":{"name":"SilentConviction","pseudonym":"Jaded-Swivel","displayUsernamePublic":true,"bio":"Low noise. High conviction.